<doc id="217563" wikidata="Q7316271" url="?curid=217563" title="Restrepia citrina">
<text>Restrepia citrina is a South American species of Orchid native to Colombia. It typically grows in the wet tropical biome. 

== Range ==
This rare epiphytic species is endemic to the cool, damp montane forests of the Eastern Cordillera of Colombia at altitudes of about 2,600 m. 

